#Text=Lansdowne ( India )
#Text=Lansdowne is a small hill station in Pauri-Garhwal District of the Garhwal region of Uttarakhand .
#Text=Described by some as the gates to the heavenly abode that is the Himalayas , Lansdowne is also one of the most unusual hill stations in India .

#Text=Far from the crowded , overdeveloped and noisy places that most of the popular hill stations of the north have become , Lansdowne has retained its quiet and serenity thanks to the presence of the local Army Cantonment Board which manages and regulates the development in the town .
#Text=The town is named after Lord Lansdowne the then Viceroy of India who visited the place in 1884 .
#Text=The town has two churches that were built in the pre-independence era , although only one , St. James , is functional .
#Text=The town also has a major Hindu temple .
#Text=The town is located at an average altitude of 1,700 metres above sea level and has cold winters , cool summers and a wet and foggy rainy season .
#Text=It experiences snowfall during the winter months .
#Text=From the snow view point on a clear day one can view great Himalayan peaks like Chaukhamba .
#Text=The town has several pre-independence era bungalows , some of them in good shape .
#Text=The connectivity is good as the roads are maintained by the army .

#Text=The hill station itself is administered by the cantonment board of the Indian Army and therefore is cleaner , much less commercialized and in good shape , although your mobile phones/wireless net may not work unless BSNL .
#Text=Any time of year is good to visit , although May/June may be a bit crowded and rooms difficult to find .
#Text=By car
#Text=Lansdowne is around 240 km from Delhi and is the nearest hill station from Delhi ( in any direction ) .
#Text=National Highway 58 runs from Delhi to Meerut and then National Highway 119 goes all the way to Lansdowne and will take you from Delhi to Lansdowne in about 6 hours .
#Text=By train
#Text=Kotdwar , the nearest railway station , is 40 km drive uphill .
#Text=Buses and taxis are available from the Kotdwar railway station directly up to the Lansdowne market ; a shared taxi charges ₹75 .
#Text=Having your own vehicle will enable you to easily visit nearby towns and temples .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Most of Lansdowne is within walking distance of the town center .
#Text=See
#Text=Bhullatal Lake .
#Text=An artificial lake dedicated to the Garhwali youth of The Garhwal Rifles who helped in construction of the lake .
#Text=Kaleshwar Mahadev Temple .
#Text=A favorite place to visit by Lord Shiva followers as well as a place of devotion for Lansdowne .
#Text=Garhwal Rifles Museum ( Darwan Singh Sanghralaya ) .
#Text=Houses artefacts from the beginning of the regiment .
#Text=The Garhwal Rifles participated in the two world wars among countless other battles throughout their more than 100 years of history .
#Text=Artefacts including photographs , arms used by regimental commanders , captured weapons , campaign history and other information are displayed in this museum .
#Text=GRRC Officer 's Mess .
#Text=Visitors are allowed upon request .
#Text=The mess contains trophies of wild animals and other regimental mementos .
#Text=Tarkeshwar Mahadev Temple .
#Text=Temple dedicated to Lord Shiva , surrounded by thick cedar and pine forests .
#Text=St. James Church .
#Text=One of two churches still in use today and popular with visitors to this hill station .
#Text=It is located on the way to Tip-n-Top .
#Text=St. Mary 's Church .
#Text=One of two churches in town .
#Text=Though it is not in use today , it is popular with visitors of this hill station .
#Text=Santoshi Mata Temple .
#Text=Located at the top of Lansdowne , this temple area offers great views of the Himalayan Range .
#Text=Snow View Point ( Tiffin Top ) .
#Text=Located close to St. Mary 's , this spot offers spectacular views of the Himalayas .
#Text=Tip-in-Top .
#Text=Offers excellent views of the surrounding shivaliks .
#Text=The War Memorial .
#Text=Located at the Parade Ground of the Garhwal Rifles Center , this is a popular attraction for visitors .
#Text=Mainly made up of Garhwali soldiers , this regiment has a distinguished record and a unique identity .
#Text=Do
#Text=Travel to ...
#Text=Bhullatal Lake ( 1 km )
#Text=Durga Devi temple ( 24 km )
#Text=Jwalpa Devi ( 47 km )
#Text=Karnva Ashram ( 14 km ) - where Shakuntala is said to have given birth to Raja Bharat
#Text=Tarkeshwar Mahadev temple ( 30 km ) - beautiful and quiet place
#Text=Buy
#Text=Though Lansdowne is a nice place , there is nothing much to buy as a souvenir .
#Text=You can spend some time in the Lansdowne Market or at the Alaknanda Market .
#Text=While in Alaknanda Market , do pay a visit to the shoe store and leather bags store , where any purchase may double as souvenir .

#Text=Do n't forget to try out mithais ( sweets/desserts ) called ' Chocolate ' ( not the usual chocolates that you buy in general stores ! ) and " Baal Mithai " that are popular to this region and available at local sweet shops .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Various small restaurants offer a decent selection of snacks , lunch and dinner , and most of them are located around Gandhi Chowk in the town centre .
#Text=Drink
#Text=All the restaurants serve your regular tea and coffee but do not expect to splurge on lavish cocktails or high end spirits !
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Vanvasa Resort
#Text=The resort is spread over in around 30 acres with 20 well-furnished cottages .
#Text=Fairydale Resort
#Text=A resort with good food , friendly staff and small rooms .
#Text=Garhwal Mandal Vikas Nigam ( GMVN ) guesthouse - Located at the tallest point of the hill station .
#Text=Offers spectacular scenic views .
#Text=SB Mount Resort ( River Side Resort ) , Village - Rothan Bhilangi , Post Office - Fatehpur ( By Personal Car / By Bus / By Train till Kotdwara ) , ☏ +919225612947 , ✉ customercare@sbmount.com .
#Text=Check-in : 13:00 , check-out : 11:00 .
#Text=SB Mount Resort is a River side resort situated in the foothills of Lansdowne .
#Text=The USP of the resort is the river which is flowing next to it .
#Text=The hotel provides bed and breakfast for the tourists .
#Text=Go next
#Text=Once you have seen places within Lansdowne , drive out to nearby towns such as Jai Hari Khal , Satpuli , Pauri and Srinagar .
#Text=A short distance off the main road from jai Hari Khal is a temple of Bhairon Dev on the top of a hill .
#Text=The trek to the temple is not very long or tiring but offers a spectacular view of the valley below .
#Text=Regular jeep taxis are available anytime from Lansdowne to Kotdwar .
#Text=Also one can get buses using G.M.O.U ltd. and Uttarakhan State Road Transport Corporation .
